<br>
Also as you level you trainer gives you alot more options language wise. but you really need about a 90 skill to be able to use a language without harsh garbleing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utuppentangledroots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuppen Tangledroots</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 10:59:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2579.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/tupsface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Language Question</span><hr size=1> There is no longer a skill cap by level on language learning.<br>
<br>
You can learn any language simply by talking in group chat with someone who knows the language.  There is no requirement to learn the basics from a trainer. <p><img src=http://bargainshoppercentral.com/saga/Tuppensig.jpg>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utuppentangledroots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuppen Tangledroots</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/icon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/20/02 11:00:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 355<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 11:03:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2579.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Language Question</span><hr size=1> There is no cap on languages anymore.  You can master all of them even if you are only level 1.<br>
<br>
Actually, a language is &quot;useful&quot; even at average (50), but you will be saying things incorrectly more frequently (the listener will &quot;hear&quot; the wrong words).<br>
<br>
Find someone who speaks a different language than you and convey to them as best you can that you wish to trade languages with him or her.  Trading is the best way to go since most younglings only do know their own language.<br>
<br>
Going to language faires is another way to learn several languages even at the same time.  Last weekend there were 2 such faires, one hosted by Saga and the other by Twilight Bastion (we both seem to have a lot of language masters).  Keep your eyes on the Events (umm the Renesaince Faire?) section for upcoming faires.  <br>
<br>
You do not need a &quot;primer point&quot; in launguages to start learning them.  There are 25 languages total.<br>
<br>
-Caillou Kyrielle<br>
&lt;Saga&gt;<br>
